{
  "card_id": "unicorn_model",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "Unicorn Model",
  "aliases": [
    "Unicorn",
    "Unicorn Setup",
    "unicorn setup"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "The Unicorn Model is an entry setup where a breaker block overlaps a fair value gap at the same price level, formed by displacement that confirms a break of structure. This confluence of two PD arrays creates a tighter, high-probability entry zone, typically used after a liquidity sweep to confirm a reversal.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Identify a valid breaker block: for bullish, a low–high–lower low–higher high sequence; for bearish, a high–low–higher high–lower low sequence; the final leg must close through the prior swing with displacement. Mark the breaker block as the series or last opposing candle(s) before the displacement (up-close candles for bullish, down-close candles for bearish).",
    "Confirm that the displacement move creates a fair value gap that overlaps with the breaker block at the exact same price level (candle wicks do not overlap, leaving a price imbalance); this confluence defines the Unicorn Model.",
    "Require a liquidity sweep preceding the displacement: a low that takes sell-side liquidity (bullish) or a high that takes buy-side liquidity (bearish).",
    "Validate the displacement by ensuring candle bodies close beyond the breaker block's mean threshold (e.g., up-close candles for longs), supporting the break.",
    "Wait for price to retrace into the overlapping breaker/FVG zone; enter on a reaction (e.g., evidence of price rejection) from this confluence.",
    "Place stop loss just below/above the breaker block's defining swing low/high or the combined PD array zone to maintain a tight risk.",
    "Target prior swing highs/lows, opposing liquidity levels, or draw on liquidity (e.g., equal highs/lows); optionally use standard deviation projections (-2, -2.5, -4, -4.5) for additional confluence targets.",
    "The pattern is applicable fractally across time frames (e.g., hourly, 5-minute, 1-minute).",
    "Check for additional confluence such as SMT divergence between correlated pairs at the swept liquidity level."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "The Unicorn Model offers a high-probability entry on a retest of the overlapping breaker block and fair value gap, enabling a tight stop just beyond the zone. It is applied after a liquidity sweep and displacement, targeting prior swing points, opposing liquidity, or draw on liquidity levels. Optional standard deviation projections can define targets. Works best with higher time frame context and on lower time frames (1–5 min).",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Entering without the full Unicorn Model structure (overlapping breaker block and fair value gap from displacement), such as relying only on SMT divergence or a standalone breaker block.",
    "Entering before confirming displacement with opposing-close candles closing beyond the breaker block's mean threshold.",
    "Placing the stop loss at the far swing high/low instead of tightly beyond the breaker/FVG confluence, making risk-to-reward targets harder to achieve.",
    "Assuming the setup is risk-free; losses can occur even with a valid unicorn entry.",
    "Failing to wait for a retrace into the zone, causing missed entries when price continues to target without retracing.",
    "Confusing any fair value gap as overlapping — it must be created by the same displacement that forms the breaker and lie within its range.",
    "Selecting the incorrect candle for the breaker block (e.g., not the last opposing candle before the displacement).",
    "Confusing Breaker Block with Order Block: the former marks the entire candle sequence including wicks, the latter only the open price.",
    "Ignoring the necessity of displacement: the breaker block must be crossed with strong momentum.",
    "Improper stop placement: placing stop at swing low instead of below breaker block, worsening risk-reward."
  ],
